Hi, in various methods of the Worksheet class a default dict is provided in the method definitions.
These can lead to problems as dicts are mutable.

See:
```
@convert_cell_args
def insert_chart(self, row, col, chart, options={}):
```
The correct method definitions should be:
```
@convert_cell_args
def insert_chart(self, row, col, chart, options=None):
    options = options or {}
    ...
```

These occurs in more places like: write_comment, set_columns, etc...

